                                                                        [38;5;244m│[39m  [1m[38;5;252m## Summary[0m
                                                                        [38;5;244m│[39m  • Problem: [38;5;189m`senseaudio`[39m bundled plugin only has ASR; no TTS.
                                                                        [38;5;244m│[39m  • Why it matters: completes the round trip in the same plugin; SenseAudio's
                                                                        [38;5;244m│[39m  [38;5;189m`/v1/t2a_v2`[39m is solid TTS and pairs with the ASR added in #66943.
                                                                        [38;5;244m│[39m  • What changed: registers a [38;5;189m`speechProvider`[39m in [38;5;189m`extensions/senseaudio/`[39m.
                                                                        [38;5;244m│[39m  Synthesizes via [38;5;189m`/v1/t2a_v2`[39m, lists system voices via [38;5;189m`/v1/get_voice`[39m, transcodes
                                                                        [38;5;244m│[39m  MP3→opus for [38;5;189m`voice-note`[39m targets. Errors split into HTTP / [38;5;189m`base_resp.status_code`[39m
                                                                        [38;5;244m│[39m  / missing-audio buckets.
                                                                        [38;5;244m│[39m  • What did NOT change: no core code; ASR untouched; streaming, telephony, voice
                                                                        [38;5;244m│[39m  cloning, text-generated voices out of scope.
